@database sort_example

@node main "Introduction to sort"

The sort object basically handles sortable objects.  Objects that can be
sorted in any way (alphanumerically, numerically, category etc) should be
derived from Sort. All one should really have to do to make their Sort object
work is to create a method 'cmp()' (see autodoc).

There is an @{" autodoc " link EMODULES:oomodules/oodoc/guides/sort/main} file available or this object.

@endnode
